.help if
usage:
    .if [expression]
    string
    .end if

This command conditionally executes a block of script if and only if the
expression is evaluated using JavaScript to true.

Examples:

SELECT * FROM MyTable ORDER BY a;
-- Check the number of rows returned from a query
.if activityCount == 0
.rem Test
SELECT 2;
.rem Test
.end if

